  "assumptions": [
    "The LinkageError is a Java 8 JVM loader-constraint bug, not a Lucene or Spring bug. Java 11+ fixed the constraint tracking for MethodHandle invocations.",
    "The reproduction uses URLClassLoader to simulate Tomcat WebappClassLoader recreation on redeploy — structurally identical to the original scenario.",
    "Spring is not required to reproduce the failure; it only managed the Lucene bean lifecycle. The bug is in Lucene's AttributeFactory$1 MethodHandle usage.",
    "lucene-core:4.10.2 is used, matching the version in the original poster's code.",
    "The test is RED on Java 21 because it asserts the Java 8 behavior (LinkageError thrown on second deploy), which no longer occurs on Java 21."
